<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-04-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-04-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="101" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d101">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 21641/15.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Carter</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-04-25"><hi rend="italic">April 25,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 29.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The department has received your No. 63 of
                            the 9th instant, in regard to the extradition of Vahan Nalbandian, and
                            commends the legation upon its manner of procedure in this case.</p>
                        <p>You will convey to the appropriate Servian and Austrian officials the
                            thanks of the department for the courtesy extended in the matter of
                            transit.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>